Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE has been exclusively retained for the sale and purchase of the Renaissance at 
the Gables, a to be built, fully entitled 269 bed multi family senior living composed of independent and assisted living. 
Located in the heart of the City of Miami, Renaissance at the Gables is located one block South of Coral Way and five blocks North of US1 within a few blocks of Coral Gables and Coconut Grove. 
The property is owned fee simple and consists of 6 parcels of land which total 1.652 acres. The property is currently serving as a fully functional 17,686 square foot banquet hall with 59 surface parking spots and a residential duplex. 
The current ownership group evaluated several different uses for this property but ultimately decided based on their analysis that the highest and best use for the property would be senior housing.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Vista Way is a 468-unit multifamily community featuring two and three-bedroom floorplans, perfect for the young family demographic that calls this area of Orlando home. Vista Way offers a unique repositioning opportunity and incredible upside through reestablishing the asset in the market by adding to the already remarkable amenity suite and bringing rents up to market. Vista Way is currently 100% vacant which will allow new ownership to begin work immediately and initiate a tactical lease-up and renovation strategy to maximize returns. Vista Way will benefit immensely from an interior value-add strategy to compete with nearby properties and improvements to the property exterior.



Vista Way is ideally located in the heart of Orlando’s entertainment district and surrounded by the area’s largest employers, offering investors a sizable opportunity at a discount to comparable properties in a submarket with extremely high barriers to entry. In addition to a plethora of dining and entertainment options in the surrounding area, the location along Interstate-4 and SR 535 grants exceptional visibility and access to Orlando’s largest employment centers.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Value-Add & Lease-Up Opportunity | 468 Units in Orlando, FL | Vista Way

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Mason offers a unique opportunity for investors to acquire an 11-story tower in the heart of St. Petersburg’s Downtown core.  Located on Central Avenue, the main thoroughfare through Downtown, offering an abundance of superb restaurants, shops, attractions, as well as other mixed-use properties, only steps away. 
 
The Mason boasts 39 residential units, plus one 2,000 sq. ft. penthouse, as well as over 4,500 sq, ft. of ground-floor retail space. Tenants of The Mason will have just a short walk to many of Downtown’s most desirable restaurants, shops, breweries, and attractions. This includes the newly renovated St. Pete Pier, a $92M project, as well as the famous Salvador Dali Museum. Both of these attracting tourists from all over the world.  The City’s largest current and proposed developments, 400 Central, the site of the 45-story mixed-use tower, and the approved Municipal Services Center redevelopment, which will be a 120,000 sq. ft mixed-use redevelopment, are both within blocks of this asset.
 
The Mason’s location in a quintessential live-work-play community presents a rare opportunity to invest in the heart of one of the nation’s top 10 real estate investment markets.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: 40 Units in St. Petersburg's Downtown Core | The Mason
